PrecisApproval of the re-appointment by the Minister of Consumer and Corporate Affairs of Georges Archer, of Westmount, Quebec, as a member of the Standards Council of Canada to hold office during pleasure for a term of three years; and designation of the said Georges Archer as President of the said Council to hold office during pleasure for a term of three years; effective November 29, 1990.
